Design and Implementation of Railway Infrastructure Inspection and Monitoring Data Management and Analysis Service Platform Based on Big Data
TAO Kai1，GUO Qiyuan1，DAI Chunping2
1.Infrastructure Inspection Research Institute，China Academy of Railway Sciences Corporation Limited，Beijing 100081，China； 2.Beijing IMAP Technology Co. Ltd.，Beijing 100081，China
Abstract In order to realize the comprehensive integration of railway infrastructure inspection and monitoring data resources，break the data barriers between various disciplines and application systems，form a panoramic view of inspection and monitoring data resources and support the asset management of the whole railway inspection and monitoring data，this paper focused on the data management business such as access （transmission），storage， governance and sharing of railway infrastructure inspection and monitoring data，designed and implemented railway infrastructure inspection and monitoring data management and integrated analysis service platform based on big data technology. While completing the comprehensive integration of inspection and monitoring data resources，it provides integrated analysis services such as registration management and scheduling application of data processing and analysis algorithms，supports fine processing and value management of data assets，and supports big data analysis applications such as infrastructure fault diagnosis，fault prediction and state evaluation. Through the practical application，the feasibility and practicability of the platform are fully verified. Key words data asset management；inspection and monitoring；integrated analysis；big data platform；railway infrastructure
（编辑：苗蕾 校对：明永玲）

